    },
    {
      "id": "lv-fcf1fd0d-beginner",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🟢 Beginner**\n**Telemetry Ingestion and Normalization**\n\nTelemetry ingestion and normalization is the process of gathering all the operational data—like performance metrics, system logs, and request traces—from all parts of an application and infrastructure. It acts as a central pipeline that collects this raw, messy data from various ",
      "x": 1320,
      "y": 1220,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-fcf1fd0d-intermediate",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🟡 Intermediate**\n**Telemetry Ingestion and Normalization**\n\nThis layer is critical because raw telemetry data is inherently chaotic, coming in different formats (e.g., JSON logs, Prometheus metrics, OpenTracing traces) from heterogeneous sources. Ingestion handles the high-throughput collection, often using agents and message queues, whil",
      "x": 1640,
      "y": 1220,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-fcf1fd0d-advanced",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🔴 Advanced**\n**Telemetry Ingestion and Normalization**\n\nTelemetry ingestion and normalization is the foundational data plane for observability architectures, focusing on transforming high-volume, high-velocity signals into actionable insights. Ingestion pipelines typically leverage distributed systems like Kafka or Pulsar to handle ba",
      "x": 1960,
      "y": 1220,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-87a7d9a8-eli5",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🍼 ELI5**\n**Semantic Signal Enrichment**\n\nImagine you have raw LEGO bricks. Semantic Signal Enrichment is adding instructions and a picture to those bricks so you know exactly what amazing spaceship you are building. It turns simple pieces into a clear plan for a great final model.",
      "x": 1000,
      "y": 1640,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-87a7d9a8-beginner",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🟢 Beginner**\n**Semantic Signal Enrichment**\n\nSemantic Signal Enrichment is the process of taking simple performance numbers (like 'server response time') and adding important context to them. Instead of just seeing a failure, we add information about which service is affected, who owns it, and what the agreed-upon goals (SL",
      "x": 1320,
      "y": 1640,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-87a7d9a8-intermediate",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🟡 Intermediate**\n**Semantic Signal Enrichment**\n\nThis process involves layering operational metadata onto raw telemetry streams. We enrich the data by joining metrics with external context, such as service dependency graphs, deployment status, and historical incident data. For instance, instead of just seeing a latency spike, w",
      "x": 1640,
      "y": 1640,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-87a7d9a8-advanced",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🔴 Advanced**\n**Semantic Signal Enrichment**\n\nSemantic Signal Enrichment is an advanced data processing technique that transforms siloed time-series telemetry into actionable, context-aware signals for observability. Implementation involves integrating disparate data sources—such as service mesh configurations, deployment ma",
      "x": 1960,
      "y": 1640,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-dcfaa698-eli5",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🍼 ELI5**\n**GenAI Reasoning and Interpretation Layer**\n\nImagine you have many puzzle pieces of information. The smart computer looks at all the pieces together to figure out what happened. It tries to guess the reason why everything is broken. It tells you how sure it is about its guess.",
      "x": 1000,
      "y": 2060,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-dcfaa698-beginner",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🟢 Beginner**\n**GenAI Reasoning and Interpretation Layer**\n\nThis layer uses Large Language Models (LLMs) to act as an intelligent interpreter of complex data. It doesn't just look at individual data points, like a single temperature reading, but correlates many different types of information—such as sensor logs, system errors, and user cl",
      "x": 1320,
      "y": 2060,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-dcfaa698-intermediate",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🟡 Intermediate**\n**GenAI Reasoning and Interpretation Layer**\n\nThe Reasoning and Interpretation Layer operates by feeding multi-modal data streams (time-series sensor data, textual logs, behavioral metrics) into an LLM. The LLM's core function is to perform cross-correlation across these disparate data sources, effectively building a tempora",
      "x": 1640,
      "y": 2060,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-dcfaa698-advanced",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🔴 Advanced**\n**GenAI Reasoning and Interpretation Layer**\n\nThis layer represents a sophisticated application of LLMs in predictive analytics, moving beyond simple pattern recognition into causal inference from noisy, high-dimensional telemetry. Implementation typically involves structured data embedding (e.g., using vector databases) fol",
      "x": 1960,
      "y": 2060,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-6c1957f1-eli5",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🍼 ELI5**\n**Knowledge Integration and Memory Layer**\n\nImagine a giant treasure chest filled with every drawing and instruction manual for building a perfect castle. This chest holds all the true history of how the castle was built. The AI looks at this chest to make sure its stories about the castle are always true and correct.",
      "x": 1000,
      "y": 2480,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-6c1957f1-beginner",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🟢 Beginner**\n**Knowledge Integration and Memory Layer**\n\nThe Knowledge Integration and Memory Layer is the foundation that gives an AI real-world context. Instead of just guessing based on patterns, this layer stores verified facts, like historical project timelines and operational instructions. It acts like a system's long-term memory",
      "x": 1320,
      "y": 2480,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-6c1957f1-intermediate",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🟡 Intermediate**\n**Knowledge Integration and Memory Layer**\n\nThis layer functions as the grounding mechanism for a Generative AI, transforming raw data into verifiable institutional knowledge. It achieves this by integrating structured data—such as incident timelines, architectural diagrams, and operational runbooks—into a persistent memor",
      "x": 1640,
      "y": 2480,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "lv-6c1957f1-advanced",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**🔴 Advanced**\n**Knowledge Integration and Memory Layer**\n\nThe Knowledge Integration and Memory Layer is a critical architectural component that serves as the institutional backbone for grounded AI systems. It moves beyond simple Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) by establishing a persistent, multi-modal memory layer that integrates c",
      "x": 1960,
      "y": 2480,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
