      "width": 280,
      "height": 130,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "st-493226f9-2",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**Step 3**\n\nStep 3: Grasp the core mechanism — how does the layered separation (Ingestion, Enrichment, Reasoning, Orchestration) actually work at a high level?",
      "x": 730,
      "y": 2490,
      "width": 280,
      "height": 130,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "st-493226f9-3",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**Step 4**\n\nStep 4: Trace through a minimal example — walk through a simple data flow (e.g., a single telemetry event) through each layer.",
      "x": 1040,
      "y": 2490,
      "width": 280,
      "height": 130,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "st-493226f9-4",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**Step 5**\n\nStep 5: Identify the parts — define the specific microservices or components within each layer and how they interact.",
      "x": 1350,
      "y": 2490,
      "width": 280,
      "height": 130,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "st-493226f9-5",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**Step 6**\n\nStep 6: Study the most common real-world use cases and patterns — analyze how this architecture is applied in observability, decision-making, and autonomous systems.",
      "x": 1660,
